result.execSummary:
The defendant Christopher D Willgrubs was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Christopher D Willgrubs is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Christopher D Willgrubs was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 2:11 Defendant Christopher D Willgrubs in court with attorney Patrick J. Costello.  Sean Edward Froelich appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Froelich: dismiss Ct#1, guilty to Ct#2. minimum fine. Costello and Def agree.   Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form is filed with the court; court reviews with Def.  Constitutional rights explained to defendant.  Exam'd re: understanding of law, penalty and rights. Def pleas guilty to Ct#2; Costello stipulates to a factual basis for conviction.   COURT ACCEPTS PLEA, FINDS DEF FREELY, INTELLIGENTLY, KNOWINGLY & UNDERSTANDINGLY MADE AND WAIVES CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHTS. Court finds and adjudicates Def guilty of Ct#2. Dismisses Ct#1. Froelich addresses sentencing. Court: orders a fine in the amount of $265.60, due in 30 days.   Appeal rights are given to the defendant.
Plea hearing on February 17, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
Plea hearing on January 20, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
Pre-trial conference on December 1, 2014 at 02:00 pm.
Pre-trial conference on November 10, 2014 at 02:00 pm.
Def pleas not guilty to both counts. Court: not guilty pleas are entered. Court goes over bond conditions with Def.

9:57 Defendant Christopher D Willgrubs in court.  Sean Edward Froelich appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Def wishes to represent himself at this time. Court goes over Waiver of Right to Attorney with Def.   Constitutional rights explained to defendant.  Exam'd re: understanding of law, penalty and rights. Deputy Herman Kreig swn, ex by Froelich. Witness ID's Def. Court: record will reflect indentification. Christopher x ex.  Court: finds the defendant probably committed the felony; binds the Def over for trial. Froelich files the information. Def is given a copy. Court reads charges and penalties. Def waives further reading.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for November 10, 2014 at 02:00 pm.
Preliminary hearing on October 6, 2014 at 09:30 am.
Def voluntarily waives his time limits for the preliminary hearing
